## ABSTRACT

Evenite is a comprehensive web-based event management platform designed to streamline and modernize event organization and participation for students and educational institutions. The system bridges the communication gap between event hosts (colleges, departments, student organizations) and participants (students) by providing a centralized, role-based ecosystem for event discovery, registration, management, and feedback.

The platform consists of three primary user roles: Students who can discover, register for, and participate in events; Hosts who can create, manage, and track events; and Administrators who oversee the entire system, manage user accounts, and ensure platform integrity. The system features gamification elements to enhance user engagement, including achievement badges, levels, and leaderboards.

Students can browse events through an intuitive dashboard, register with one-click functionality, track their attendance history, collect digital certificates, and provide feedback through customizable review forms. Hosts have access to comprehensive event management tools including registration tracking, attendee management, analytics dashboards, and certificate generation capabilities. The admin panel provides oversight of all platform activities, user verification systems, and system analytics.

Evenite integrates modern web technologies including React.js for a responsive frontend, Node.js with Express for a robust backend, and MongoDB for flexible data storage. The platform ensures security through JWT token authentication, email and phone verification processes, and student ID document verification. Cloudinary integration enables efficient image and document storage with automatic optimization.

By combining digital event management, social networking features, and gamification elements, Evenite creates a transparent and efficient digital event ecosystem that enhances student engagement, improves event organization, and strengthens campus community connections.

